  "text": "Amygdalin (Figure 1 ) is a major component of apricot kernels, bitter almonds and peach, plum, pear and apple seeds [CITATION_1] . The amount of cyanogenic glycosides in plants varies with plant species and environmental effects [CITATION_2] . For example, apricot seeds and bitter almonds contain approximately 20-80 μmol/g and 100 μmol/g of amygdalin, respectively.",
